                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d885">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.01/534: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Yugoslav Government in Exile</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-15T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 15—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Yugoslav Series. King Peter yesterday left London for Cairo accompanied by
                    the members of his Government.</p>
                <p>They expect to arrive in about a fortnight, and the Government will thereafter be
                    established in Cairo instead of in London.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
